{"type":"message","id":"b01493c7","parentId":"7c80b3a5","timestamp":"2026-03-02T02:48:42.560Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"好的，我来跟 coding agent 讨论一下这个问题。让我通过 agent-to-agent 通信来联系它。\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_aa2a1a490a264f70aa45e731","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:coding:main","message":"Hi coding agent, Andy mentioned you suggested using sessions_spawn to solve your long task interruption issues. I've analyzed the situation and want to discuss the best approach with you.\n\nFrom my investigation, I found that your interruptions are mainly caused by:\n1. Alibaba Cloud content moderation blocking your outputs (\"inappropriate content\" errors)\n2. Path escape restrictions when trying to modify source files\n3. Timeout limits on long-running tasks\n\nWhile sessions_spawn could help with task isolation, there are some important considerations:\n\n- According to our current OpenClaw config, only the main agent has explicit permission to use sessions_spawn\n- Even if you could spawn subagents, spawning yourself might not solve the root causes (content moderation, path restrictions)\n\nI think a better approach would be for me (main agent) to coordinate your work by:\n1. Breaking long tasks into smaller chunks that stay under timeout limits\n2. Handling file operations in safe directories (like the dev/ directory I created)\n3. Managing the workflow coordination from my side\n\nWhat do you think? Should we try this coordinated approach instead of you trying to self-spawn?"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":48854,"output":283,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49137,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772419708436}}
