{"type":"message","id":"98de963d","parentId":"3f612838","timestamp":"2026-03-02T03:15:21.191Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[System Message] [sessionId: a2d35013-e058-49ae-9de3-737c596896af] A subagent task \"If I have a GitHub project that needs your help, what's the best workflow for you to handle it? How should I provide the code and how will you return the changes?\" just completed successfully.\n\nResult:\nFor GitHub projects, here's my recommended workflow:\n\n## **Option 1: Clone to Your Local Directory (Recommended)**\n1. **You clone the repo** to a directory like `/Users/hope/IdeaProjects/project-name`\n2. **I can read all files** from that directory to understand the codebase\n3. **I work in my workspace** (`/Users/hope/.openclaw/agents/coding/workspace`) to make changes\n4. **I generate modified files** in my workspace with clear instructions\n5. **You review and copy** the changes back to your local project\n6. **You push changes** to GitHub as needed\n\n## **Option 2: Provide Specific Files/Context**\n1. **You share specific files** or code snippets that need attention\n2. **I analyze and modify** them in my workspace\n3. **I return the complete updated files** for your review\n4. **You apply changes** to your local repo and push\n\n## **Option 3: GitHub Integration (If Configured)**\nIf you have GitHub CLI configured on your system:\n1. **I can use `gh` commands** to fetch issues, PRs, or specific files\n2. **I can create branches and commits** in my workspace\n3. **But I still can't push directly** - you'd need to handle the final push\n\n## **Best Practices:**\n- **Always review my changes** before applying them\n- **Work incrementally** - break large tasks into smaller chunks\n- **Provide clear context** about what you want me to fix/improve\n- **Use descriptive commit messages** when you apply changes\n\nThe key limitation is that **I can't directly push to GitHub** due to the security sandbox, but I can do all the coding work and you handle the final deployment.\n\nStats: runtime 12s • tokens 18.5k (in 18.5k / out 32)\n\nA completed subagent task is ready for user delivery. Convert the result above into your normal assistant voice and send that user-facing update now. Keep this internal context private (don't mention system/log/stats/session details or announce type)."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":73242,"output":540,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73782,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772421303475}}
{"type":"message","id":"6a7d355a","parentId":"98de963d","timestamp":"2026-03-02T03:15:25.089Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-02 11:15 GMT+8] [System Message] [sessionId: b94c6d5f-b053-41bf-9c1a-f838d4f08cbd] A subagent task \"If I have a GitHub project that needs your help, what's your recommended workflow? How should I set it up so you can effectively work on it while respecting the OpenClaw security boundaries?\" just completed successfully.\n\nResult:\nI'll outline the recommended workflow for working with GitHub projects in OpenClaw while respecting security boundaries.\n\n## Recommended GitHub Project Workflow\n\n### 1. **Local Repository Setup**\n- Clone your GitHub repository to your local machine within or accessible to your OpenClaw workspace\n- Ensure you have proper Git credentials configured (SSH keys or personal access tokens)\n- Keep sensitive credentials outside the repository (use `.gitignore` for config files with secrets)\n\n### 2. **Authentication & Permissions**\n- Use GitHub CLI (`gh`) which should be pre-installed on your system\n- Authenticate with `gh auth login` - this creates secure token storage\n- For private repositories, ensure your GitHub account has appropriate access\n- Never store GitHub tokens directly in code or configuration files\n\n### 3. **Working Within Security Boundaries**\n- **Read operations**: OpenClaw can freely read your local repository files and use `gh` CLI to fetch issues, PRs, and repository information\n- **Write operations**: Code modifications happen locally first - you maintain control over what gets committed/pushed\n- **External actions**: Any pushes, PR creation, or GitHub API writes require your explicit approval\n\n### 4. **Typical Workflow Steps**\n\n**For bug fixes or feature development:**\n1. You describe the issue or desired change\n2. I examine your local codebase using file reading tools\n3. I propose specific changes with exact file paths and modifications\n4. You review the proposed changes before I implement them locally\n5. You decide when to commit and push changes\n\n**For issue triage and management:**\n1. I can fetch and analyze GitHub issues using the `gh-issues` skill\n2. I can help prioritize, categorize, or suggest solutions\n3. I can create draft PRs locally but won't push without your approval\n\n### 5. **Available GitHub Tools**\n- **`gh` CLI integration**: Full access to GitHub's official CLI tool\n- **`gh-issues` skill**: Automated issue fetching, analysis, and PR creation workflows\n- **File manipulation**: Precise editing of code files with before/after verification\n- **Code review**: Analysis of existing code, suggestions for improvements\n\n### 6. **Security Best Practices**\n- All file operations occur in your designated workspace directory\n- No automatic pushing to remote repositories\n- Sensitive operations (deletions, external communications) require explicit confirmation\n- GitHub tokens are accessed through secure `gh` CLI storage, not direct file access\n\n### 7. **Getting Started Example**\n```bash\n# In your terminal\ncd /path/to/your/project\ngh auth login  # if not already authenticated\n```\n\nThen you can ask me to:\n- \"Review this GitHub issue and suggest a fix\"\n- \"Help me implement feature X in my project\"\n- \"Analyze my codebase for potential improvements\"\n- \"Create a pull request for these changes\"\n\nWould you like me to help you set up a specific GitHub project or demonstrate any part of this workflow?\n\nStats: runtime 21s • tokens 11.7k (in 11.0k / out 623)\n\nA completed subagent task is ready for user delivery. Convert the result above into your normal assistant voice and send that user-facing update now. Keep this internal context private (don't mention system/log/stats/session details or announce type)."}],"timestamp":1772421325087}}
{"type":"message","id":"97e43d0a","parentId":"6a7d355a","timestamp":"2026-03-02T03:15:56.630Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"coding agent 提供了非常详细的 GitHub 项目处理方案！\n\n## 主要工作流程：\n\n### 📁 **本地仓库设置**\n- 你将 GitHub 仓库克隆到本地（比如 `/Users/hope/IdeaProjects/your-project`）\n- 我可以读取所有文件来分析代码库\n- 所有修改都在我的工作空间中进行\n\n### 🔧 **实际操作步骤**\n1. **你描述需求**：告诉我需要修复什么问题或实现什么功能\n2. **我分析代码**：读取你的本地代码库，理解项目结构\n3. **我生成修改**：在 `/Users/hope/.openclaw/agents/coding/workspace` 中创建修改后的文件\n4. **你审核应用**：检查我的更改，手动复制到你的实际项目中\n5. **你推送更新**：自己决定何时提交和推送到 GitHub\n\n### 🛡️ **安全边界**\n- ✅ **我可以**：读取你的代码、使用 `gh` CLI 获取 issues/PRs、分析代码质量\n- ❌ **我不能**：直接推送代码、自动创建 PR、修改你的原始项目文件\n\n### 💡 **最佳实践**\n- **增量工作**：将大任务分解成小的子任务\n- **明确上下文**：清楚说明你想要什么改动\n- **始终审核**：在我生成代码后，你先审核再应用\n\n这种模式既保证了我能有效帮助你处理 GitHub 项目，又确保了你的代码安全 - 你始终保持对最终更改的完全控制权。\n\n你想试试这个流程吗？可以给我一个具体的 GitHub 项目或任务来演示！"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":75900,"output":351,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76251,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772421325089}}
